results.raw: Two People Shot at Mall of America at 60 East Broadway, Minneapolis, Minnesota, 55425
results.title: Two People Shot at Mall of America

-MsHlaJsJmXaiaMRCHHt.text: Incident reported at Mall of America .

-MsHlaP4fc2j_VPcjeMd.text: The Mall of America is under lockdown following reports of a shooting.

-MsHoUbONDXsa-gXaR_J.text: Police advise two people were shot. One victim was shot in the shoulder and the second victim was shot in the leg. Shell casings have been recovered.

-MsHuZOMtdfaNtUKHoBv.text: According to a tweet from the Bloomington Police, the scene at the Mall of America is secure after a brief lockdown. The two victims sustained injuries which are not life-threatening. Officers are no longer searching for the suspect at the Mall of America.

nib.text:
The Mall of America underwent a lockdown Friday evening following reports of a double shooting, officials said. 

At around 5 p.m., police responded to reports of a shooting inside the mall. 

Immediately, MOA personnel and security placed the building under lockdown with many guests still inside. 

According to a Tweet from the Bloomington police, two people were shot but sustained injuries not believed to be life-threatening. 

Officials later reported in a briefing that the shooting occurred an argument between two men escalated to gunfire. One man sustained an injury to the leg and the other was grazed.

The investigation is ongoing.
